        <h2 id="brownie">Recipe #1</h2>
        <h3>Brownie's!</h3>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/35/Chocolate_brownies.jpg/1200px-Chocolate_brownies.jpg" alt = "Plate full of brownies" width = "203">
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 25m prep, 35m cook</li>
            <li>Serves: 183 calories</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour an 8-inch square pan.
In a large saucepan, melt 1/2 cup butter. Remove from heat, and stir in sugar, eggs, and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat in 1/3 cup cocoa, 1/2 cup flour, salt, and baking powder. Spread batter into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Do not overcook.
To Make Frosting: Combine 3 tablespoons softened butter, 3 tablespoons cocoa, honey, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, and 1 cup confectioners' sugar. Stir until smooth. Frost brownies while they are still warm. (All credit for this recipe goes to "Angie" from allrecipe's.com)
        
